Date Published:2020-03-21 00:00:00      
The identities of the deceased could not be confirmed immediately At least 12 people were killed and seven others injured in a collision between a truck and a human haulier in Lohagara upazila of Chittagong.  The incident took place on the Chittagong-Cox's Bazar Highway around 9:30pm on Saturday.  The identities of the deceased could not be confirmed immediately, confirmed Lohagara Upazila Nirbahi Officer Tausif Ahmed. Meanwhile, the injured were taken to Chittagong Medical College Hospital.
